job_title: Sr. Data Insights Analyst - Remote | WFH
desc: We are seeking a Senior Data Insights Analyst to join our team and lead the development of our business intelligence and analytical capabilities. In this role, you will play a vital part in understanding and enhancing our product usage and customer experience. Collaborating closely with our Product, Customer, and Engineering teams, you will also be responsible for the evaluation, selection, and implementation of data analytical tools to facilitate data collection, processing, and visualization.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong>Lead and Enhance Analytical Capabilities: Drive the development of our analytical capabilities to produce comprehensive analyses of product usage and customer experience.<br><br>Define Key Performance Indicators (KPIs): Create and regularly update KPIs and business metrics to monitor progress toward achieving our business objectives and goals.<br><br>Collaborate Cross-functionally: Work with our Product, Customer, and Engineering teams to establish the necessary data and analytical foundation, including data pipelines, data quality assurance checks, and automated reporting.<br><br>Select and Employ Data Analytics Tools: Evaluate, select, and utilize key data analytics tools to address business challenges and inform critical decisions.<br><br>Effective Data Storytelling: Regularly communicate and present concise, actionable insights using effective data storytelling techniques to inform all product and business partners.<br><br><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong>Relevant Experience: A minimum of 5 years of prior work experience in product, customer, and operations analytics, with proficiency in tools like Mixpanel, Heap, Amplitude, and similar.<br><br>Data Proficiency: 5+ years of experience in data querying languages (e.g., SQL) and statistical programming (Python and/or R).<br><br>Data Infrastructure: 3+ years of experience working with large datasets, data modeling, and data pipelines using tools like Databricks, DBT, Looker, Snowflake, and Tableau.<br><br>Analytical Storytelling: 3+ years of experience in deriving actionable insights from analysis and analytical storytelling.<br><br>Educational Background: A degree in MIS, Mathematics, Engineering, Data Science, or other quantitative fields.<br><br>Strong Analytical Skills: Detailed-oriented with exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills.<br><br>Project Management: Strong project management experience and skills.<br><br>Life at Our Company<br><br>Customer and Employee-Centric Culture: We prioritize the satisfaction of both our customers and employees.<br><br>Rapid Growth: Our customer base is expanding, and we're growing quickly.<br><br>Remote and Flexible: Our team has embraced remote and flexible work arrangements from day one.<br><br>Flexible Schedules: We work hard while embracing flexible schedules.<br><br><strong>Benefits<br><br></strong>Remote Flexibility: Enjoy the flexibility of remote work options.<br><br>Mental Health Support: Access mental health benefits and an Employee Assistance Program (EAP).<br><br>Technology: Receive a company laptop (Mac or PC).<br><br>Health and Wellness: Medical, dental, and vision benefits, Life &amp; supplemental life insurance, Health Savings Account (HSA), and Flexible Savings Account (FSA).<br><br>Travel Discounts: Take advantage of vacation, hotel, food, retail, and car rental discounts.<br><br>Pet and Legal Services: Access pet insurance and legal services.<br><br>Insurance Discounts: Benefit from auto, home, and renters insurance discounts, as well as critical illness insurance.<br><br><strong>Compensation<br><br></strong>Attractive Package: Our compensation package includes a competitive base salary, company performance bonus, stock options, and a comprehensive health and benefits package.<br><br>Remote Work<br><br>This role offers the flexibility of remote work.<br><br>Employment Type: Full-Time

<strong>Summary:<br><br></strong>We are looking for someone to assist with dashboard creation, to help ensure synchronization of critical sales pipeline data across two systems, and support tech tools implementation. The primary responsibility of the Associate will be understanding the key data elements being tracked across both systems, and with guidance from the manager, develop and implement a standardized process to download data from one system and manually upload into a second system. Once the process is determined to be stable, the Associate will be on point to regularly implement the data sync across the two systems. In addition, the person will need to flag records where a straightforward update is not possible due to discrepancies in record identifiers, and work with the manager to follow-up with data owners to correct data as needed before uploading.<br><br><strong>Skills:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Attention to detail</li><li>Proactive, problem-solving mindset</li><li>Ability to work independently and manage ones time</li><li>Ability to accurately document and record issues for follow-up, and commitment to follow-through to closure</li><li>Judgement on when to ask for guidance and when to carry on independently</li><li>Experience with computer applications such as Excel, Word, Outlook, SharePoint<br><br></li></ul><strong>Education and Experience:<br><br></strong><ul><li>High School Diploma or GED required, Associate or Bachelor’s Degree preferred</li><li>3-7 years related experience required<br><br></li></ul><strong>Compensation:<br><br></strong>The pay rate range above is the base hourly pay range that Aditi Consulting reasonably expects to pay someone for this position (compensation may vary outside of this range depending on a number of factors, including but not limited to, a candidate’s qualifications, skills, competencies, experience, location and end client requirements).<br><br><strong>Benefits and Ancillaries:<br><br></strong>Medical, dental, vision, PTO benefits and ancillaries may be available for eligible Aditi Consulting employees and vary based on the plan options selected by the employee.

Bachelors degree with 5+ years experience in data cleansing, extracting, reviewing and loading experience within Oracle Fusion Cloud ERP applications<p><br></p>Experience in data conversion testing between Microsoft Dynamics and Oracle Fusion<p><br></p>Experience in defining data cleansing approaches, implementing Oracle Utilities and Oracle Data Conversion tools like FBDI and HDL template uses<p><br></p>Strong knowledge of ERP systems and understanding of data flow between applications<p><br></p>Proficiency with Oracle and SQL/PLSQL<p><br></p>Proven experience in design, configuration, testing, and support of ERP data<p><br></p>Advance skills in MS Office (Access, Excel, PowerPoint, Word)<p><br></p>English required at an advanced proficiency level

<strong>Responsibilities<br><br></strong><ul><li> Understand the business: Track operational performance, provide insights and recommendations</li><li> Ownership of Analytical projects: Support company-wide programs through ownership of analytical projects</li><li> Build efficient and scalable ETL processes to extract, transform, and load data from various sources into our data warehouse. Able to write ad-hoc data pipelines</li><li> Performance Optimization: Continuously improve data processing and analysis efficiency. Identify and implement optimizations to enhance query performance, reduce processing time, and increase overall productivity</li><li> Build dashboards and automated reports, working proficiently with data visualization and querying/analysis tools (e.g., Tableau, SQL, Python)</li><li> Own data tables, and work with stakeholders to ensure available data is accurate, consistent, and timely</li><li> Own technical implementations and documentation associated with datasets and strive for 100% accuracy</li><li> Possibility to learn &amp; implement advanced analytics tools for optimization (e.g., Cloud hosting, Job automation, Artificial Intelligence techniques, Natural Language generation)<br><br></li></ul><strong>Basic Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> BS degree in a quantitative discipline</li><li> 4+ years of experience working with data in a business setting, including data management, data architecture process execution, operations, reporting, or analytics<br><br></li></ul><strong>Preferred Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li> Ability to leverage numbers and insights to influence &amp; This role 4-5 month contracting role offers the flexibility to work remotely.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities:<br><br></strong>As a Business Intelligence Analyst, your key responsibilities include —<br><br><ul><li>Translating business problems into data-driven questions </li><li>Performing deep dive analysis using diverse data sources </li><li>Collaborating with stakeholders to deliver valuable insights </li><li>Tracking and reporting on key metrics to support decision-making </li><li>Developing reporting solutions and data stories </li><li>Staying updated on industry trends and best practices </li><li>Gathering and analyzing data to provide actionable insights <br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications:<br><br></strong>To be considered for the Business Intelligence Analyst role, you should possess the following qualifications —<br><br><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in math, engineering, statistics, data science, or a related field </li><li>Proven experience in data analytics, business intelligence, or similar roles </li><li>Proficiency with SQL and visualization tools (e.g., PowerBI, Tableau, Looker) </li><li>Familiarity with digital analytics tools (e.g., Google Analytics, Adobe Analytics) </li><li>Knowledge of quantitative and qualitative analysis, as well as basic statistics </li><li>Excellent communication and presentation skills <br><br></li></ul><strong>Benefits:<br><br></strong><ul><li>Competitive compensation rate of $50 per hour </li><li>Option for fully remote work </li><li>Opportunities for professional growth and development </li><li>Collaborative and dynamic work environment <br><br></li></ul>——————————<br><br><strong>Note: Qualified candidates will be contacted within 2 business days of application. If an applicant does not meet the above criteria, we will keep your resume on file for future opportunities and may contact you for further discussion.</strong>

Laguna Games is the developer of Crypto Unicorns, the #1 NFT project on Polygon, and now one of the fastest-growing games. We are looking to hire an experienced Data Engineer to join our team. You are self-motivated, goal-orientated, and a strong team player. As a Data Engineer, you will be responsible for designing, building, and maintaining the data infrastructure that supports our gaming platform. You will work closely with our product, engineering, and data science teams to collect, process, and analyze large amounts of data generated by our gaming platform to inform our business decisions and improve user experience. You will work and innovate at the forefront of web3 gaming, bringing together unique technologies to deliver a new gaming experience.<br><br>As a Data Engineer at our Web3 Gaming Startup, Key Responsibilities:<br><br><ul><li>Develop and maintain the data pipeline that ingests, processes and stores large amounts of data generated by our gaming platform</li><li>Design and build scalable data solutions that support the real-time analytics and reporting needs of the business</li><li>Collaborate with the product, engineering and data science teams to identify and implement data-driven solutions to improve user engagement, retention and monetization</li><li>Build and maintain data models, data warehouses and data marts to support business intelligence and reporting needs</li><li>Ensure data quality, integrity and security across all data sources and systems</li><li>Monitor and optimize data performance and scalability, and identify and resolve any data-related issues and bottlenecks</li><li>Keep up-to-date with the latest trends, tools and technologies in data engineering and apply them to improve our data infrastructure<br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related field</li><li>3+ years of experience in data engineering or related field</li><li>Experience with big data technologies such as Hadoop, Spark, Kafka, and Elasticsearch</li><li>Strong proficiency in SQL, Python and/or Java programming languages</li><li>Experience with cloud-based data solutions such as AWS, Azure or Google Cloud</li><li>Familiarity with data modeling, ETL/ELT processes, data warehousing, and business intelligence tools</li><li>Understanding of blockchain technology and its use in gaming platforms is a plus</li><li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, and ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams<br><br></li></ul>If you are passionate about data engineering and excited about the opportunity to work in a fast-paced and dynamic startup environment, we would love to hear from you!<br><br>Laguna Games is the developer of Crypto Unicorns, a new blockchain-based game centered around awesomely unique Unicorn NFTs that players use in a fun farming simulation and in a variety of exciting battle loops. As game developers, we are excited to move away from the extractive nature of Free-2-Play to foster and nurture community-run game economies. Crypto Unicorns is our first digital nation and we are extremely excited to build it in tandem with our player community!<br><br>We are headquartered in San Francisco, CA but operate as a remote company with locations around the world. We offer competitive compensation along with health benefits (medical, dental, and vision), 401k retirement savings, open paid time off, and a remote work support stipend.<br><br>Learn more here!<br><br>https://laguna.games<br><br>https://www.cryptounicorns.fun

<strong>Description</strong><p><br></p><strong>Job Summary</strong><p><br></p>The Data Visualization Analyst serves as the research and technical expert to create views of institutional data related to key functional areas for a diverse population of users. This role will provide data visualization solutions to support institutional analytics and reporting needs. The position focuses on building and managing dashboards and analytical reports that drive cross functional initiatives related to university business operations and evaluation/research studies. This role is responsible for the full cycle development, implementation, enhancement, and troubleshooting of dashboards hosted by IRSA and the Campus Data Warehouse. This position works closely with university executives, stakeholders, and various business partners including IRSA and the Information Technology departments to provide solutions that are relevant and consequential in meeting their analytical needs. This position reports to the Senior Director of Institutional Research and Strategic Analytics in the Office of Institutional Research.<p><br></p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Lead the development of dashboards hosted by IRSA to automate data reporting using census and real-time data (e.g., PeopleSoft)</li><li>Support the Campus Data Warehouse dashboards or the like to create visual consistency between IRSA and CDW dashboards as well as ensuring any data across the university’s dashboards are accurate, reconciled, and secure</li><li>Develop and update templates, content, definitions, references, resources, and process documentation related to the publishing of university dashboards</li><li>Design, update, and implement web features, enhancements and contents through CMS and HTML scripting or similar</li><li>Maintain and enhance the university’s Required Data Elements dashboard to support Program Planning, Assessment, and Accreditation</li><li>Enhance self-service capabilities by providing data reports, infographics, fact sheets or the like based on client’s needs</li><li>Lead the development of Campus Profile Report using innovative visualization techniques</li><li>Create visualized work products to grow IRSA’s reporting and business intelligence capabilities</li><li>Contribute relevant information to support data governance and ensure appropriate use of work products by users</li><li>Takes responsibility for developing protocols to ensure and monitor the accuracy, integrity, security, and functionality of IRSA’s hosted data services and products and participates in troubleshooting, as needed</li><li>Act as the subject matter for dashboard-related questions and inquiries</li><li>Educate and train customers to use IR dashboards as an informational and analytical tool</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Knowledge, Skills &amp; Abilities</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Proficient with Tableau and other BI tools. Experience with writing Structured Query Language (SQL) to create reports with a detail-oriented approach to data visualization</li><li>Comprehensive knowledge of database management systems and skilled programming abilities in SQL or other query languages</li><li>Ability to manage and account for multiple programs’ operational needs and provide recommendations for areas requiring improvement</li><li>Ability to apply analytic mindset and use appropriate techniques to evaluate the effectiveness of policies, programs, and practices</li><li>Proficient writing and presentation skills in English including the ability to communicate technical details to nontechnical audiences</li><li>Ability to support academic leaders related to enrollment, program planning, assessment, scheduling and resource management practices</li><li>General knowledge of SPSS, SAS, Stata, and/or R to perform basic statistical analyses</li><li>Ability to accurately compile custom data sets. Ability to produce well-formatted, easy-to-read data reports and extracts</li><li>Ability to perform data management and stewardship to obtain desired results</li><li>Ability to develop techniques for handling a large variety of detailed data and ability to analyze these data</li><li>Demonstrated ability to plan, organize, and coordinate the workflow of assigned projects to deliver high-quality professional work products</li><li>Ability to communicate with constituents in a professional and respectful manner</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Equivalent to graduation from a four-year college or university. Additional qualifying professional experience may be substituted for the required education on a year-for-year basis</li><li>Three years of progressively responsible technical research or statistical experience including or supplemented by one year in the interpretation and graphic presentation of data. Graduate study in the social sciences, economics, mathematics, statistics, public or business administration or engineering may be substituted for the required experience on a year-for-year basis.</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong><p><br></p><ul><li>Master’s Degree in data visualization, information design, media design, education, social sciences, economics, mathematics, statistics, public administration, business, data analytics, engineering, computer or data science or other related fields</li><li>More than three years of professional and proficient experience in designing and developing high-impact visualization solutions. Expert user in Tableau including in SQL writing scripts to analyze data and perform data queries, creating reports with quantitative modeling, detail-oriented approach to data visualization and validation</li><li>Experience in front end web development and technologies such as HTML5, ES6, TypeScript, JavaScript, and CSS</li><li>Experience transforming qualitative outcomes into digestible and consumable formats</li><li>Extensive experience in written and visualization communication skills</li><li>Experience in higher education research, project management, enrollment management and/or scheduling concepts and procedures</li><li>Experience running statistical models and predictions (such as linear and binary regressions) on higher education data sets</li><li>Experience working directly in Institutional Research/Institutional Effectiveness, Assessment, and/or Data Analytics/Business Intelligence offices</li></ul><p><br></p><strong>Compensation</strong><p><br></p>Classification: Research Technician III<p><br></p>Anticipated Hiring Range: $6,223/month - $6,589/month<p><br></p>CSU Salary Range: $4,789/month - $8,664/month<p><br></p>San José State University offers employees a comprehensive benefits package typically worth 30-35% of your base salary.
